result.formatted_address: 3, The Phoenix, 23 Luard Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Sing Kee Seafood Restaurant

reviews.text:
One of my favorite Chinese restaurants in Hong Kong that is also a coveted Michelin  ranked establishment.

Always ask about the specials offered as they definitely are great choices while the menu staples are consistent time and time again whenever I get a chance to visit.

Reservations absolutely a must to avoid disappointment as they are rarely not full for dinner even on weekdays.

A place you won't regret. My favourite Chinese restaurant for dinner.

Visited again on 23/7/19 again, still very good.

My niece took me there for my birthday.  It serves Cantonese style food.  Considering this is in Hong Kong and most Chinese restaurants are good, I would still rate this 5 stars.  The owener came by the table and told my niece that we had ordered too much and made some recommendations. Very friendly chap.  The food and the service were good. The price was also reasonable. Worth a visit.

Super disappointed. Which makes me doubt about Michelin recommendation. Or maybe they just praised about the Central shop. This Wanchai one is a big -ve:  No space between tables. Noisier than wet market. Dishes taste amateurish.  Food served at a rushy pace that urge guests to leave quick.  Any random pick would be a better option.

After a long period absent here, this place is full with office workers in the vicinity well before 12:30 pm. Again the delicious Chinese stir fried style dishes are a must to try. Though only fried rice on this occasion plus steam eggs and chicken with mushroom are all superb.
